---
title: Installation
---

.main-content
  .container
    %h1
      %i.fa.fa-cloud-download
      Installation

    %p
      It is recommended to use the latest version from the git master branch.

    %table.table.table-condensed
      %tr
        %td(colspan="2")
          %h3
            %i.fa.fa-windows
            Windows
          %p
            All binary packages are unofficial third-party builds, except as noted.
            The first-party CI builds are intended mainly for testing and may be
            missing certain features.

      = package_row 'Windows builds by shinchiro (git)',
                    'https://github.com/shinchiro/mpv-winbuild-cmake/releases',
                    :"cloud-download"
      = package_row 'Windows builds by zhongfly (git)',
                    'https://github.com/zhongfly/mpv-winbuild/releases',
                    :"cloud-download"
      = package_row 'First-party builds by GitHub CI (latest commit)',
                    'https://nightly.link/mpv-player/mpv/workflows/build/master',
                    :"cloud-download"
      = package_row 'Scoop', 'https://scoop.sh/#/apps?q=mpv&id=b05b47128464d8969416289383fbfc69a47353e3'
      = package_row 'Scoop (git)', 'https://scoop.sh/#/apps?q=mpv&id=72b493d66b164257cc87db56a4f581688afc13be'
      = package_row 'Chocolatey', 'https://chocolatey.org/packages/mpvio'
      = package_row 'MSYS2', 'https://packages.msys2.org/base/mingw-w64-mpv'
      = package_row 'Compilation instructions', 'https://github.com/mpv-player/mpv/blob/master/DOCS/compile-windows.md'

      %tr
        %td(colspan="2")
          %h3
            %i.fa.fa-apple
            macOS
          %p
            All binary packages are unofficial third-party builds, except as noted.
            The first-party CI builds are intended mainly for testing and may be
            missing certain features.

      = package_row 'First-party builds by GitHub CI (latest commit)',
                    'https://nightly.link/mpv-player/mpv/workflows/build/master',
                    :"cloud-download"
      = package_row 'macOS builds by stolendata', 'https://laboratory.stolendata.net/~djinn/mpv_osx/', :"cloud-download"
      = package_row 'MacPorts', 'https://ports.macports.org/port/mpv/'
      = package_row 'Homebrew (without application bundles)', 'https://formulae.brew.sh/formula/mpv'

      %tr
        %td(colspan="2")
          %h3
            %i.fa.fa-terminal
            Source code
          %p
            If you want bleeding edge functionality, git versions of FFmpeg
            or if a package for your platform is unavailable/outdated,
            you can build mpv from source code. The helper build
            scripts are recommended for most users since they produce a static
            build together with FFmpeg, libplacebo and libass.

      = package_row 'git repository', 'https://github.com/mpv-player/mpv', :"github-alt"
      = package_row 'Latest stable release', 'https://github.com/mpv-player/mpv/releases/latest', :"github-alt"
      = package_row 'Helper build scripts for *nix systems', 'https://github.com/mpv-player/mpv-build', :"github-alt"

      %tr
        %td(colspan="2")
          %h3
            %i.fa.fa-linux
            Linux packages
          %p
            Distributions usually package outdated, unmaintained, and unsupported versions of mpv.
            This is especially true for popular distributions like Debian and Ubuntu.
            It is recommended to use mpv-build or third-party packages instead.
            All of these packages are unofficial.

      = package_row 'Arch (official package)', 'https://archlinux.org/packages/extra/x86_64/mpv/'
      = package_row 'Gentoo (official package)', 'https://packages.gentoo.org/packages/media-video/mpv'
      = package_row 'Arch (AUR, git package)', 'https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/mpv-git/'
      = package_row 'Arch (AUR, mpv-build package)', 'https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/mpv-build-git/'
      = package_row 'Debian multimedia', 'https://deb-multimedia.org/dists/testing/main/binary-amd64/package/mpv'
      = package_row 'Ubuntu and Debian (apt repository)', 'https://fruit.je/apt'

      %tr
        %td(colspan="2")
          %h3
            %i.fa.fa-mobile
            Mobile platforms

      = package_row 'Android', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=is.xyz.mpv'

      %tr
        %td(colspan="2")
          %h3
            %i.fa.fa-floppy-o
            Other platforms

      = package_row 'FreeBSD (Freshports)', 'https://www.freshports.org/multimedia/mpv'
      = package_row 'NetBSD', 'https://ftp.netbsd.org/pub/pkgsrc/current/pkgsrc/multimedia/mpv/index.html'
      = package_row 'OpenBSD', 'https://cvsweb.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/cvsweb/ports/multimedia/mpv/'
      = package_row 'Haiku', 'https://depot.haiku-os.org/mpv'

